becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>]</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00F72FA4"><w:t xml:space="preserve"> to discuss the following questions:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2EE0D8DF" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00F72FA4" w:rsidRDefault="00F72FA4" w:rsidP="00F72FA4"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becteachertalkparagraph"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>What is a community? (Sample response: A group of people who live, work, or play together; a group of people who share similar interests or wants.)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="335B8770" w14:textId="02ECB2F7" w:rsidR="00F72FA4" w:rsidRPr="007C3BC1" w:rsidRDefault="00F72FA4" w:rsidP="00F72FA4"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becteachertalkparagraph"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">What is a writing community? </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="007C3BC1"><w:t>(Sample response: People who write together, share writing experiences.)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="21B8E7A4" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00F72FA4" w:rsidRDefault="00F72FA4" w:rsidP="00F72FA4"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">Circulate while students discuss, then have a few students share their thinking. Engage students in the </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00D43473"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becroutine"/></w:rPr><w:t>[Agree, Disagree, Add More Routine]</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> to respond and build off others' ideas.  </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0D195F9D" w14:textId="4D9B4A8E" w:rsidR="00F72FA4" w:rsidRDefault="00F72FA4" w:rsidP="00F72FA4"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">Tell students that throughout the unit they will participate in activities to help build their writing community. Today, students will learn and participate in a protocol called the </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="000B5206"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>Gallery Walk Protocol.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7509212C" w14:textId="2ADA3588" w:rsidR="00471E89" w:rsidRDefault="00471E89" w:rsidP="00471E89"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="beclessonc-hd"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00471E89"><w:t>Teach Gallery Walk Protocol</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4C708D62" w14:textId="091E37D0" w:rsidR="00471E89" w:rsidRDefault="00471E89" w:rsidP="00471E89"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00471E89"><w:t xml:space="preserve">Explain that a gallery is usually a room to display art. In galleries, people often move from one piece of art to another as they discuss the art and its meaning. In a similar way, when participating in the </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00D1300E" w:rsidRPr="00D1300E"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>[</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00D1300E"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>Gallery Walk Protocol</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00D1300E" w:rsidRPr="00D1300E"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>]</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00D1300E"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>,</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00471E89"><w:t xml:space="preserve"> students will move from one material to another. At each material they will discuss and/or write a response to the material.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3B61BA36" w14:textId="657CB8E6" w:rsidR="00471E89" w:rsidRPr="00471E89" w:rsidRDefault="00471E89" w:rsidP="00471E89"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00471E89"><w:t xml:space="preserve">Display and read aloud the </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="006713E8" w:rsidRPr="006713E8"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>[</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="006713E8"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>Gallery Walk Protoco</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="006713E8"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>l].</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="18B93B90" w14:textId="3F563721" w:rsidR="008F33D7" w:rsidRDefault="00A145A7" w:rsidP="008F33D7"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becslide"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Gallery Walk Protocol</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1BC8506E" w14:textId="71EFE8D0" w:rsidR="00A145A7" w:rsidRPr="00A145A7" w:rsidRDefault="00A145A7" w:rsidP="005B199A"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becslidetype"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Graphic organizer</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="67B713A3" w14:textId="387313DD" w:rsidR="005455A2" w:rsidRDefault="00A145A7" w:rsidP="005455A2"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becslidespec"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00A145A7"><w:t>Insert thumbnail of the Gallery Walk Protocol</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3403F92C" w14:textId="731EF15D" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becteachertalkparagraph"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>Today, you will use sticky notes during step three to respond to questions about writing. For step three you will follow these directions.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6F5FC940" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRPr="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becnumberedlist"/><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr><w:t>Read the question on the poster and any sticky notes that have been added.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="48B88958" w14:textId="6391282F" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRPr="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becnumberedlist"/><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Discuss the question with the other people in your group. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6A79E0CA" w14:textId="19F222EF" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRPr="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becnumberedlist"/><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Write down your response to the question on a sticky note.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7D014F6A" w14:textId="3197E9DA" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becnumberedlist"/><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becteachertalkcharacter"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Add your sticky note to the poster.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="24F36729" w14:textId="6F315D1F" w:rsidR="00C22E37" w:rsidRDefault="00C22E37" w:rsidP="00C22E37"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becteachertalkparagraph"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00C22E37"><w:t>As we share our ideas and read the ideas of others, it is important that we are kind and respectful so that everyone feels safe sharing what they really think or feel in response to the prompts and questions. This helps us build a trusting and safe writing community.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="625E871F" w14:textId="0BB85786" w:rsidR="00EF604E" w:rsidRDefault="00EF604E" w:rsidP="00EF604E"><w:r><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becicon"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">ACCESS </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00EF604E"><w:t>To support community building, gauge student openness to share responses and provide an option for students to place their responses in a box or envelope as they move around the gallery.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5C70870D" w14:textId="7B3716C1" w:rsidR="00525BDB" w:rsidRDefault="00525BDB" w:rsidP="00EF604E"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00525BDB"><w:t>Stand next to each of the questions posted around the room and read each one aloud.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6AA4142D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00525BDB" w:rsidRDefault="00525BDB" w:rsidP="00525BDB"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becbulletedlist"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Why does writing matter?</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="33A6FB0F" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00525BDB" w:rsidRDefault="00525BDB" w:rsidP="00525BDB"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becbulletedlist"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>What have you written that you are proud of?</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="27FA39D4" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00525BDB" w:rsidRDefault="00525BDB" w:rsidP="00525BDB"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becbulletedlist"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>How can we support each other to become better writers?</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0749E69F" w14:textId="05A4A17B" w:rsidR="00525BDB" w:rsidRPr="00EF604E" w:rsidRDefault="00525BDB" w:rsidP="00525BDB"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becbulletedlist"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">What </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="00D45829"><w:t xml:space="preserve">different types of writing do you see in </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">your own life? </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0EAD407F" w14:textId="1DA11479" w:rsidR="00AB4606" w:rsidRDefault="00550DB0" w:rsidP="00E11765"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becactivity"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00550DB0"><w:t>Gallery Walk Protocol</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="10BED043" w14:textId="039901D2" w:rsidR="000829B8" w:rsidRDefault="000829B8" w:rsidP="000829B8"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becactivitysubcontentcode"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>TKTKTKTKTK</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="330B5ABB" w14:textId="59BB2B5E" w:rsidR="008F33D7" w:rsidRPr="006A3CF4" w:rsidRDefault="001E2280" w:rsidP="008F33D7"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becactivitytype"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Introduction</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="55A48748" w14:textId="39D2F81A" w:rsidR="008F33D7" w:rsidRDefault="00746BBF" w:rsidP="008F33D7"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becactivityduration"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>13</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="23E6BCB6" w14:textId="35D9AB6A" w:rsidR="008F33D7" w:rsidRDefault="008F33D7" w:rsidP="008F33D7"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becactivitynumber"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>3</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5A3966C0" w14:textId="17D38C81" w:rsidR="002C32A5" w:rsidRDefault="008F44A0" w:rsidP="002C32A5"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="becLOstudentfocus"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="008F44A0"><w:t>SL.CC.1.</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="008F44A0"><w:t>4.i</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="008F44A0"><w:t xml:space