RPr="008F44A0"><w:t>SL.LU.2.4.iii Use language and style appropriate to the topic</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t>.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7D3F8E9E" w14:textId="7F9EAE9E" w:rsidR="00C76141" w:rsidRDefault="008F44A0" w:rsidP="008F44A0"><w:r w:rsidRPr="008F44A0"><w:t>Distribute four sticky notes to each student.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="67A94FB3" w14:textId="3F99F35A" w:rsidR="008F44A0" w:rsidRDefault="008F44A0" w:rsidP="008F44A0"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">Guide students through the </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00071412"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becprotocol"/></w:rPr><w:t>Gallery Walk Protocol.</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Make sure to prompt students to share their ideas with others at each poster before writing and posting their responses. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="63FA4DB1" w14:textId="656380C2" w:rsidR="008F44A0" w:rsidRDefault="008F44A0" w:rsidP="008F44A0"><w:r><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>As needed, pause during the protocol to review expectations for how students use appropriate voice levels and move around the classroom safely.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3C8F4DE8" w14:textId="6A0182F0" w:rsidR="00483A63" w:rsidRDefault="00483A63" w:rsidP="00483A63"><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00483A63"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becicon"/></w:rPr><w:t>iELD</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="008F44A0" w:rsidRPr="008F44A0"><w:t>Provide support by partnering students with an English proficient or in a small group so that students can dictate to a partner to scribe their ideas on the provided resource.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="00D122F9" w14:textId="4125094C" w:rsidR="00483A63" w:rsidRDefault="00433211" w:rsidP="00433211"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00433211"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="becicon"/></w:rPr><w:t>ACCESS</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> </w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00433211"><w:t xml:space="preserve">Provide other materials such as index cards